  "body": "I was setting up a private Ethereum node on MacOS for testing purpose, using `puppeth`.\r\nTo exit the puppeth interface using control + c, doesn't work for me.  Is there any other way to exit?\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.10.11-stable`\r\nOS & Version: macOS v 11.6.1\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nThe terminal should exit anytime using `control+c`\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nDoesn't exit\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nTry puppeth on MacOS terminal.\r\n\r\nSample \r\n```\r\nSpecify your chain/network ID if you want an explicit one (default = random)\r\n> 4224\r\nINFO [11-08|16:03:48.583] Configured new genesis block \r\n\r\nWhat would you like to do? (default = stats)\r\n 1. Show network stats\r\n 2. Manage existing genesis\r\n 3. Track new remote server\r\n 4. Deploy network components\r\n> 2\r\n\r\n 1. Modify existing configurations\r\n 2. Export genesis configurations\r\n 3. Remove genesis configuration\r\n> 2\r\n\r\nWhich folder to save the genesis specs into? (default = current)\r\n  Will create chainskills.json, chainskills-aleth.json, chainskills-harmony.json, chainskills-parity.json\r\n> \r\nINFO [11-08|16:04:07.878] Saved native genesis chain spec          path=chainskills.json\r\nINFO [11-08|16:04:07.879] Saved genesis chain spec                 client=aleth path=chainskills-aleth.json\r\nINFO [11-08|16:04:07.880] Saved genesis chain spec                 client=parity path=chainskills-parity.json\r\nINFO [11-08|16:04:07.881] Saved genesis chain spec                 client=harmony path=chainskills-harmony.json\r\n\r\nWhat would you like to do? (default = stats)\r\n 1. Show network stats\r\n 2. Manage existing genesis\r\n 3. Track new remote server\r\n 4. Deploy network components\r\n> ^C\r\n> ^C\r\n> ^C\r\n> ^C\r\n```\r\n",
